# OpenAPI: refresh merged Cloud spec after core API changes

When you change any of the globbed files in **slugbase** in a way that affects **documented or actual integrator-facing HTTP API** (paths, methods, auth notes), you must refresh the **Cloud deployment** merged OpenAPI before marking the task complete.

## Do this (Cloud deployment repo)

1. From the **Cloud** repository root run:

   ```bash
   npm run openapi:bundle
   ```

2. If **`openapi/openapi.cloud.yaml`** changed, include it in the commit (with any related Cloud changes).

## Which core source the bundle uses

- **After `npm run pack:cloud` + `npm install` in Cloud** (normal core handoff): the script uses `openapi.selfhosted.yaml` from **`@mdguggenbichler/slugbase-core`** in `node_modules` — correct for shipped tarball.
- **Only edited `openapi.selfhosted.yaml` in slugbase without packing**: set **`SLUGBASE_CORE_OPENAPI`** to the absolute path of `slugbase/backend/openapi/openapi.selfhosted.yaml` when running `openapi:bundle`, so you do not merge from a stale installed core copy.

## Relation to version sync

If your change also requires a **core version bump and `pack:cloud`**, follow [core-cloud-version-sync.mdc](core-cloud-version-sync.mdc) first; step **5** there already includes `npm run openapi:bundle` after `npm install`.
